<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 7:39PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Haralson and south central Polk Counties through 815 PM EDT...
At 738 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Felton, or near
Buchanan, moving southwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph and up to penny sized hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Antioch, Eubank Lake, and Felton.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
